purpose: The commit fixes a bug in the Bluetooth HCI layer by preventing queuing commands when HCI_UNREGISTER is set.
The commit removes an unnecessary include file from n_hdlc.c and replaces it with a more appropriate one.
The commit updates documentation for a new store metric 'N/A'.

The commit fixes a race condition in hugetlb_unmap_file_folio when locks are dropped and reacquired in the correct order. It also ensures that all VM_MAYSHARE vmas have a vma lock present for fault/truncate synchronization, and updates the sharing code to make sure vma lock is indeed a condition for pmd sharing.
The commit adds two new supplies - AVDD and MICVDD - to the rt5682s codec used by sc7180-trogdor-kingoftown.dtsi.
The commit fixes a resource leak in zorro7xx_remove_one() by adding an iounmap() call to the remove function.
The commit removes an unused field from a struct in the mlx5e_async_ctx structure.
The commit changes the type of a struct member from unsigned to signed in order to avoid warnings from static analysis tools such as smatch when the key is NULL.
The commit sorts CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS in a specific order.
The commit replaces an open-coded check for CAN-FD mode by a newly introduced function mcp251xfd_is_fd_mode().
The commit adds a new feature to the kernel test suite that skips tests when RTC is not present.
The commit removes a redundant assignment to variable bytes in midi.c. The value is never read from 'bytes' and can be safely removed.

This commit decouples the presence of rcuscale from the presence of RCU Tasks in a CONFIG_PREEMPT_NONE=y kernel. This means that if rcuscale is built-in or as a module, it will not be built with RCU Tasks.
The commit removes a duplicated 'be split' in spte.h file, which is related to x86/mmu module.

The commit reverts populating dcn315 clk table based on dcfclk due to a no read situation caused by pmfw filling out the table when dcfclk states are disabled. This is done to prevent underflow until a better solution is coded.
The commit adds a compatible string for the Bifrost Mali-G31 GPU in the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC.
The commit renames a struct from pcie_port to dw_pcie_rp in the DW PCIe core driver to make it more consistent with other names.
The commit fixes a clang -Wformat warning by changing the format specifier from %#06hx to %x in the netdev_dbg function call.
The commit fixes a bug in the MIPS branch range check by casting the upper bound to long to do signed compare.
The commit removes a specific case from a function in the kernel driver for the RTL8188EU Wi-Fi adapter. This is part of an ongoing effort to simplify and optimize the code.
The commit declares non-global symbols as static to fix sparse warnings introduced while adding errata.
The commit changes the display/msm bindings to drop bogus interrupt flags cell on MDSS nodes. This is a bug-fixing commit as it fixes a bug in the code that was causing incorrect behavior.
The commit changes the way arrays are allocated in struct ctrl_ref to allow for changing array size from a driver.
The commit adds support for several new SoCs and PMICs to the socinfo driver.
The commit recognises all possible chip cuts (A-P) instead of printing 'unknown' when greater than E.
The commit removes a custom software enable count from PRCMU clocks in the core. The core already keeps a software enable count.
The commit moves the pt_ops macro to adjacent #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL and group first type usage cases into one.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA hardware to be able to add functioning I2C nodes later.
The commit fixes comments in the thermal driver code for RZG2L platform. It also corrects a typo and follows coding style guidelines.
The commit fixes an infinite loop in release_swfw_sync by acquiring a hardware semaphore before releasing resources.
The commit updates the pcm3168a driver to use modern terminology for clocking, as part of moving away from old style defines.
The commit removes an unnecessary hack that was previously used to detect swap files.
The commit adds support for GTP echo responses to the kernel module gtp-u.
The commit replaces cpumask_next_* functions with cpumask_first_* where appropriate. This patch also creates a new function called cpumask_first_zero().
The commit removes a call to 'dtim_assoc' IOVAR in the host driver when STA roams from one AP to another. This is done because the firmware no longer supports this call and it will always fail.
The commit adds a new board config for the alc5682 codec without speaker amplifier. It follows the Intel BT offload design by connecting the alc5682 to SSP0.
The commit fails zerocopy send requests for protocols that don't support it, do the same for zerocopy sendmsg.

The commit adds a new feature to the kernel documentation by adding a preamble to the xeCJK.sty file that tests for its existence before loading it. This is useful on RHEL 9 and its clone distros where texlive-xecjk does not work at the moment due to a missing dependency.
The commit adds a new feature to the kernel's checkpatch tool by allowing macros with complex values to be enclosed in parentheses.
The commit replaces simple-KMS helpers with regular atomic helpers in drm/simpledrm. No functional changes.
The commit adds a jpeg decoding worker to ensure that three HWs run in parallel in MT8195.

The commit removes pointless VPRINTK() calls from libata and ata_scsi_dump_cdb(), as they can be retrieved from scsi tracing. This is a bug-fixing commit (BFC) that fixes a bug present in the source code, defined as a software fault that manifests as a failure when running in a certain way the version of the system previous to the commit.

The commit adds support for zstate during extended vblank in the AMD display driver. The commit includes a full update of the stream update when entering freesync and restores default values when exiting freesync.
The commit fixes a CFI failure in kfd_destroy_mqd_cp() by updating the function pointer prototype to match reality.
The commit changes the name of a property from 'reset' to 'resets', which is a bug fix for an incorrect property name.
The commit silences an array-bounds warning on GCC 12 in the ath9k driver for wireless networking.
The commit simplifies code by using pm_runtime_resume_and_get instead of pm_runtime_get_sync.
The commit splits out fixed file installation and removal from the io_uring code into a separate filetable module. The helpers take a ctx rather than an io_kiocb to apply to the ring itself.
The commit splits the G1 and G2 nodes into separate decoder blocks that can be independently fused out. The new DT + old kernel isn't a supported configuration.

The commit removes a macro that was previously used to define common configuration options for Intel WiFi devices. The commit is likely to improve the code's readability and maintainability by reducing unnecessary complexity.
